</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000I.xml"
addr="erct-000I"
title="Functor between precategories">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called (<fr:em><fr:strong>full</fr:strong></fr:em>, <fr:em><fr:strong>faithful</fr:strong></fr:em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0029.xml"
addr="erct-0029"
title="Surjection">surjections</fr:link>, <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-003K.xml"
addr="erct-003K"
title="Embedding">embeddings</fr:link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <fr:em>full</fr:em> and <fr:em>faithful</fr:em> functor as <fr:em><fr:strong>fully faithful</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p><fr:p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <fr:em><fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">properties</fr:link></fr:em> of a functor.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
